
## Chengdu Linkwise Future Technology

Application to become an approved third-party manufacturer as per HIP19. The submission of a HIP19 application does not guarantee approval. All questions must be answered, any missing information will result in delays.
## Summary:
Chengdu Linkwise Future Technology Co., Ltd. is a manufacturer specializing in Internet of Things communication equipment based on LoRaWAN, including R&D, manufacturing and sales. It was found in 2019 and has participated in the maintenance and construction of LoRaWAN official open-source server multiple times over the years. All engineers have more than 5 years of LoRaWAN R&D experience, and the company was certified as a high-tech enterprise in China as of 2021. It also has a number of patents and intellectual property rights and has obtained ISO9001 quality certification in 2022. Products run on projects of several large state-owned enterprises in China, such as National Energy and China Tobacco, and others.
## Company Information (required)
* What is the company name?
 Chengdu Linkwise Future Technology Co., Ltd.
* How long has the company been in business? 
3+ years
* What kind of products have you created? (list specific products, include links if possible)
LoRaWAN Indoor Gateway G7x Series, G9x Series (5000 units/year)
LoRaWAN Outdoor Waterproof Gateway G6x Series , G8x Series (2,000 units/year)
LoRaWAN Gateway RF Module M302x(20,000 units/year)
LoRaWAN Wireless terminal moduleA5x Series, A7x Series (120,000 units/year)
LoRaWAN Wireless Temperature and Humidity Meter (4,000 units/year)
LoRaWAN Wireless human body infrared sensor (2,000 units/year)
LoRaWAN Wireless door sensor (30,000units/year)
LoRaWAN DTU (8,000 units/year)
LoRaWAN RTU (1,000 units/year)
* How many have you sold? 
More than 150,000 units (gateways,modules and sensors) total annually.
* What brought you to the Helium Network? 
Our company has been working on LoRaWAN related projects. Last year many customers came to our company requesting to purchase Helium gateways. After investigating, we felt that the Helium project could solve the problems of difficult and costly deployment of IoT base stations. In China, IoT base stations either use the NB network, which is monopolized by three major telecom companies or use individual small-scale deployment base stations. The former has problems of expensive fees, unstable network, and insufficient signal coverage. The latter has the problems of non-standard personal base station protocol and low base station utilization. Helium perfectly solved these two issues. We hope to become a third-party manufacturer of Helium.

## Product Information (required)
* What is this product's model name? (Hotspot models with different hardware will need a separate HIP19 application.)
LW Orca-M100
* Is this is a Light Hotspot or a 5G Hotspot? (New applications should be for Light Hotspots or 5G Hotspots)
Yes, it's a Light Hotspot.
* Is this model for indoor, outdoor, or both? (If there are two different models for indoor and outdoor, list them separately.)
It is for Indoor and Outdoor
* Provide a brief description of the product:
The indoor light gateway integrates MT7688 as the core of the system, equipped with a baseband processing chip SX1302, which realizes 8-channel upload and 1-channel delivery. The transmit power is up to 27dBm, the receiver sensitivity is up to -140dBm@SF12, it supports global frequency plans, local and cloud upgrade, and configurations.
The outdoor light gateway is based on the indoor light gateway, adding a waterproof shell, adding a high-gain fiberglass waterproof antenna, using POE power supply, and reserving the GPS installation location, which is convenient for later updating to SX1303. 
Both indoor and outdoor gateways are identical in configuration and operation.
* What is your approximate price point?
$350
* What is your expected production and delivery timeline? 
Start of Q1 2023

