![figure1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/109646661/180889055-504f59ec-2dff-4146-9209-9426112be64c.jpg)
Indoor PCB
2.Start the gateway, and the gateway starts to synchronize the router address, indicating that the gateway can connect to the helium server, as shown in the following figure;
![figure1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/109646661/180889056-65ddda7f-508d-462e-93e4-9d970e2494f1.jpg)
3.The gateway receives the data sent by the forwarder, indicating that the 1302 module has started to work and has received data from the terminal, as shown in the following figure;
![figure1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/109646661/180889040-13b6759d-2188-4e73-83b9-53195a754bb7.jpg)
4.The data terminal is registered on the Helium server, and the terminal sends a data packet with an ACK reply. The Helium server receives the terminal data and passes the verification, and the terminal receives the confirmation packet sent by the server, which proves that the server connection is successful, as shown in the following figure.
Note: Our test gateway name is perfect-orchid-locust
