## Risks & Challenges (required)
Please tell us about some of the challenges that would prevent these products from becoming a reality and how you might address them.
The current production challenge lies in the supply chain, mainly purchasing chips and transporting the product.
Currently, we have signed long-term supply orders with suppliers to mitigate the risk of chip shortage and will always maintain a minimum reserve of chip inventory to ensure that products are available for sale.
Further, due to the impact of the epidemic, we will establish a second assembly test point in Shenzhen for backup, in case the city affects shipments due to epidemic control from China government.

